description:
This is a 21 minute workout called 'Total Body Circuit' from the channel Rina Thomas.
The workout falls under Strength/Calisthenics.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Other and Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Warrior Workout and The Adrenaline Rush vibe.
The The Warrior Workout vibe means Unleash your inner beast. Sweat-dripping, heart-pounding, primal energy. This is especially good for Days when you want to destroy stress and feel invincible. The The Adrenaline Rush vibe means Heart-racing, full-body intensity, unpredictable challenges. This is especially good for Those who crave challenge, variety, and adrenaline..
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Moderate.

Original workout description: Power through an invigorating 20-minute total body circuit workout with Rina! Start with a two-minute warm-up, then dive into two six-minute AMRAP blocks featuring banded side squats, walkout planks, uneven push-ups, and glute bridges. No dumbbells are neededâ€”just your Hydrow, mat, and a resistance band. Rina's dynamic style will keep you energized and motivated, ensuring you finish strong and feel accomplished!
